  {
    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "If you look at failed videos, there are at least 3 different root causes. @matifali Wouldn't it be more convenient to create a new issue for things we spot in logs? Ideas:\r\n\r\n1. `coderd: failed to query logs`:\r\n\r\n```\r\n2023-08-29T17:31:42.4335743Z [WebServer] 2023-08-29 17:31:42.431 [erro]  coderd: failed to query logs  job_id=063319c7-e61a-422f-a28e-e0178c8bb10c  request_id=a0e41ac8-757a-488b-b51a-d4bc2073ccd6 ...\r\n2023-08-29T17:31:42.4345839Z     error= error writing to websocket:\r\n2023-08-29T17:31:42.4346435Z                github.com/coder/coder/v2/coderd.(*logFollower).query\r\n2023-08-29T17:31:42.4399679Z                    /home/runner/actions-runner/_work/coder/coder/coderd/provisionerjobs.go:459\r\n2023-08-29T17:31:42.4401214Z              - failed to write msg: failed to close writer: failed to write fin frame: failed to write frame: WebSocket closed: failed to acquire lock: context deadline exceeded\r\n2023-08-29T17:31:42.4402712Z [WebServer] 2023-08-29 17:31:42.432 [warn]  coderd: failed to close webscoket  job_id=063319c7-e61a-422f-a28e-e0178c8bb10c  request_id=a0e41ac8-757a-488b-b51a-d4bc2073ccd6  error=\"failed to close WebSocket: failed to write control frame opClose: WebSocket closed: failed to acquire lock: context deadline exceeded\"\r\n```\r\n\r\n2. `Error with Permissions-Policy header`\r\n\r\n```\r\n2023-08-29T17:31:02.4788739Z \u00b7Console: Error with Permissions-Policy header: Unrecognized feature: 'battery'.\r\n2023-08-29T17:31:02.4789512Z Console: Error with Permissions-Policy header: Unrecognized feature: 'document-domain'.\r\n2023-08-29T17:31:02.4790057Z Console: Error with Permissions-Policy header: Unrecognized feature: 'vr'.\r\n```\r\n\r\n3. Split logs per test case.\r\n4. Log backend API calls.\r\n",
